Inventory Test Cases.Unnamed: 1: Manage Cycle Count Variances
Inventory Test Cases.Unnamed: 4: User (typically a supervisor or manager) will enter the "Approve Variances" UI through a laptop or desktop
Inventory Test Cases.Unnamed: 5:
Depending on which action was taken, stock units will be updated to reflect what was counted, remain the same and cycle count task will be complete, or remain the same but generate a new cycle count task for the same location. 

The process will be repeated until either there is no variance detected, or the variance is accepted in "manage cycle count variances".

Inventory Test Cases.Unnamed: 4: A list of variances will be displayed.  A variance is any time a qty is entered that differs from what Deposco has listed in the system.
For each record you will see the item, counted qty, variance qty, reason code, and other relevant data. The columns listed can be adjusted.

Whoever is managing the variances can select the tasks and accept (stock units for that item/location will be updated based on what was counted), reject (stock unit for that location/item will remain with the same qty they had before the cycle count), or re-count (no change is made to the stock unit yet, and cycle count task is sent back to the floor to be re-counted).
